                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6359 Wolfram Ore/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-12T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1933—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>281. Your 657, August 9, 9 a.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d640fn10">Not printed.</note>
                    In conversations in New York on August 6 and 7 with Soong, officer of the
                    Department took occasion to comment adversely on the grant of a monopoly for
                    export of wolfram. Soong expressed the view that the principle involved in the
                    action taken by Chinese authorities was wrong and said he would see what he
                    could do about rectifying the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
